From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pa1q device tree <noreply@local>
Date: Tue, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] twrp: fast statfs-only /data+system size refresh via ORS
 (no GUI freeze)

PROBLEM
  TWRP computes partition sizes ONCE at startup (Update_System_Details),
  which on the S25 (pa1q) runs BEFORE our decrypt.sh has mounted /data.
  At that point /data is encrypted/absent so Size=Free=0 -> "Internal
  Storage (0 MB)" forever, because nothing recomputes sizes after the
  script mounts /data. The only existing recompute is the "Refresh Sizes"
  button -> Update_System_Details(), which for /data calls
  Get_Folder_Size() (a recursive walk of every file under /data) and
  freezes the GUI for 3-5 seconds.

  The storage size itself (Size/Used/Free) is actually cheap: it comes
  from statfs() (Get_Size_Via_statfs), which reads the filesystem
  superblock counters - microseconds, no file walk. The freeze is purely
  the Get_Folder_Size() backup-size estimate, which is glued into the same
  Update_Size() function and cannot be triggered separately via ORS.

FIX (additive, two files, ~40 lines, nothing existing is modified)
  1) partitions.hpp: declare a new TWPartitionManager method
     Update_Data_Size_Fast().
  2) partitionmanager.cpp: implement it - statfs() on /data (and the
     mounted system partition), write BOTH the DataManager display vars
     (tw_storage_free_size / tw_backup_data_size / tw_backup_system_size)
     AND the live TWPartition fields (Size/Used/Free/Backup_Size). The
     latter is what the Select-Storage and Backup dropdowns read on the
     fly in Get_Partition_List(), so they get fixed too. No Get_Folder_Size
     -> ZERO freeze. TWPartitionManager is already a friend of TWPartition,
     so it can write the private size fields directly.
  3) gui/gui.cpp: add a new inline ORS command word "refreshdatasz",
     handled in the same fast path as dumpstrings/reloadtheme - i.e. WITHOUT
     setting tw_busy, so the GUI is never blocked.

  Our ramdisk scripts then send `echo refreshdatasz > /system/bin/orsin`
  after a successful /data mount (decrypt.sh) and after a GUI remount
  (remount_data). Instant, freeze-free, on both first decrypt and remount.

  "Internal Storage" on this device IS the /data partition itself
  (Setup_Data_Media sets Is_Storage on /data), so updating dat->Free fixes
  the storage dropdown directly - there is no separate storage object.

  Files touched (for revert):
    bootable/recovery/partitions.hpp
    bootable/recovery/partitionmanager.cpp
    bootable/recovery/gui/gui.cpp
---
 partitionmanager.cpp | 35 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 partitions.hpp       |  1 +
 gui/gui.cpp          |  4 ++++
 3 files changed, 40 insertions(+)

